President Trump delivered remarks at the 37th Annual National Peace Officers' Memorial Service, paying tribute to law enforcement officers who lost their lives in the line of duty. He honored specific individuals and their families, highlighting their courage and sacrifice. The president emphasized the importance of supporting and protecting law enforcement and called on Congress to take action to secure the borders, support border agents, and end attacks on police officers. He also expressed gratitude for the men and women in law enforcement and their commitment to keeping communities safe.